{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-11224/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-11224"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:12:24"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["Man and woman sit at table"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11224/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-11224","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11224/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-11224"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11224/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11224/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11224/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11224/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11224/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11224/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11224/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11224/canvas/1/90e73482-4feb-4b9e-bde4-ec21e81da4e4","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T19:26:57.361Z","creator":"lucia","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>In a continuation of the haunted house theme, Cyril suggests that Reynolds is turning Alma into a “ghost”—someone who lives with them but isn’t truly part of their lives and whom Reynolds ignores. The “phantom thread” is thus also Alma. She is an element of Reynolds’s life that is hard to pin down.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>While Cyril and Alma are often competing for Reynolds’s attention, here Cyril reveals that she has “grown quite fond” of Alma even as Reynolds has grown frustrated with her. Reynolds and Cyril are incredibly enmeshed siblings; partners in business and living together, they often seem to come as a unit. While Alma has failed to gain Reynolds’s full affection, in her seduction of him she seems to have won the goodwill of his sister.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11224/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:60.75949367088608,88.35443037974686,302.44725738396625,196.4556962025316"}}}]}]}]}